#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np21"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:0.4"
msgid "Pattavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:0.5"
msgid "21. Pattasikkhāpada"
msgstr "21. The training rule on bowls"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:0.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-np21.1, pts-vp-en2.113, ms1V_2252
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bahū patte sannicayaṃ karonti."
msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of six were storing many bowls."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.3"
msgid "Manussā vihāracārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā passitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "When people who were walking about dwellings saw this, they grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā bahū patte sannicayaṃ karissanti,"
msgstr "“How can the Sakyan ascetics store many bowls?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.5"
msgid "pattavāṇijjaṃ vā samaṇā sakyaputtiyā karissanti āmattikāpaṇaṃ vā pasāressantī”ti."
msgstr "Will they start up as bowl merchants or set up a bowl shop?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms1V_2253
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.6"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.7"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.8"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.9"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū atirekapattaṃ dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six have extra bowls?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, pts-vp-pli3.243, ms1V_2254
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.10"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.11"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, atirekapattaṃ dhārethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.12"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.13"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.14"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, atirekapattaṃ dhāressatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you have extra bowls?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.15"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.16"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.16a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc4, ms1V_2255
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.17"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu atirekapattaṃ dhāreyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk keeps an extra bowl, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc5, ms1V_2256
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:1.18"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc6, pts-cs-bu-np21.2, pts-vp-en2.114, ms1V_2257
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato ānandassa atirekapatto uppanno hoti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards a bowl was given to Venerable Ānanda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.2"
msgid "Āyasmā ca ānando taṃ pattaṃ āyasmato sāriputtassa dātukāmo hoti."
msgstr "but he wished to give it to Venerable Sāriputta"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.3"
msgid "Āyasmā ca sāriputto sākete viharati."
msgstr "who was staying at Sāketa."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato ānandassa etadahosi—"
msgstr "Knowing that the Buddha had laid down a rule against keeping an extra bowl, Venerable Ānanda thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.5"
msgid "“bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.6"
msgid "‘na atirekapatto dhāretabbo’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.7"
msgid "Ayañca me atirekapatto uppanno."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.8"
msgid "Ahañcimaṃ pattaṃ āyasmato sāriputtassa dātukāmo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.9"
msgid "Āyasmā ca sāriputto sākete viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.10"
msgid "Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?"
msgstr "“What should I do in this situation?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.11"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "He told the Master, and the Master said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.12"
msgid "“Kīvaciraṃ panānanda, sāriputto āgacchissatī”ti?"
msgstr "“How long is it, Ānanda, before Sāriputta returns?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.13"
msgid "“Navamaṃ vā, bhagavā, divasaṃ dasamaṃ vā”ti."
msgstr "“Nine or ten days, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.14"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.15"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, dasāhaparamaṃ atirekapattaṃ dhāretuṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, you should have an extra bowl for ten days at the most."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.16"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.16a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_2258
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.17"
msgid "“Dasāhaparamaṃ atirekapatto dhāretabbo."
msgstr "‘A monk should have an extra bowl for ten days at the most."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:2.18"
msgid "Taṃ atikkāmayato nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "If he keeps it beyond that, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, pts-cs-bu-np21.3, ms1V_2259
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.1"
msgid "Dasāhaparamanti"
msgstr "For ten days at the most:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.2"
msgid "dasāhaparamatā dhāretabbo."
msgstr "it should be kept for ten days at a maximum."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms1V_2260
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.3"
msgid "Atirekapatto nāma"
msgstr "An extra bowl:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.4"
msgid "anadhiṭṭhito avikappito."
msgstr "a bowl that is not determined, nor transferred."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, pts-vp-en2.115, ms1V_2261-2262
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.5"
msgid "Patto nāma"
msgstr "A bowl:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.6"
msgid "dve pattā"
msgstr "there are two kinds of bowl:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.7"
msgid "ayopatto mattikāpattoti."
msgstr "the iron bowl and the clay bowl."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="gloss">
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.8"
msgid "Tayo pattassa"
msgstr "And there are three kinds of bowl:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.9"
msgid "vaṇṇā ukkaṭṭho patto majjhimo patto omako patto."
msgstr "the large bowl, the medium bowl, and the small bowl."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.10"
msgid ""
msgstr "Anything larger than this is not a bowl, nor anything smaller."

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.11"
msgid "Ukkaṭṭho nāma patto"
msgstr "The large bowl:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.12"
msgid "aḍḍhāḷhakodanaṃ gaṇhāti catubhāgaṃ khādanaṃ tadupiyaṃ byañjanaṃ."
msgstr "it takes half an _āḷhaka_ measure of rice, a fourth part of non-staple food, and a suitable amount of curry."

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.13"
msgid "Majjhimo nāma patto"
msgstr "The medium bowl:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.14"
msgid "nāḷikodanaṃ gaṇhāti catubhāgaṃ khādanaṃ tadupiyaṃ byañjanaṃ."
msgstr "it takes a _nāḷika_ measure of rice, a fourth part of non-staple food, and a suitable amount of curry."

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.15"
msgid "Omako nāma patto"
msgstr "The small bowl:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.16"
msgid "patthodanaṃ gaṇhāti catubhāgaṃ khādanaṃ tadupiyaṃ byañjanaṃ."
msgstr "it takes a _pattha_ measure of rice, a fourth part of non-staple food, and a suitable amount of curry."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.17"
msgid "Tato ukkaṭṭho apatto, omako apatto."
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc12, pts-vp-pli3.244, ms1V_2263
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.18"
msgid "Taṃ atikkāmayato nissaggiyo hotīti"
msgstr "If he keeps it beyond that […] entailing relinquishment:"

# NOTE: According to the commentary this means the tenth dawn after one received the bowl, see [](Sp.3.639.27)
#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.19"
msgid "ekādase aruṇuggamane nissaggiyo hoti."
msgstr "it becomes subject to relinquishment at dawn on the eleventh day."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.20"
msgid "Nissajjitabbo saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The bowl should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.21"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbo."
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.116
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.22"
msgid "Tena bhikkhunā saṃghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "After approaching the Order, that monk should put his upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the senior monks. He should then squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.23"
msgid "“ayaṃ me, bhante, patto dasāhātikkanto nissaggiyo."
msgstr "‘Venerables, this bowl that I have kept over ten days is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.24"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti."
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’"

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.25"
msgid "Nissajjitvā āpatti desetabbā."
msgstr "After relinquishing it, he should confess the offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.26"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena āpatti paṭiggahetabbā,"
msgstr "The confession should be received by a competent and capable monk."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.27"
msgid "nissaṭṭhapatto dātabbo—"
msgstr "The relinquished bowl is then to be given back:"

#. HTML: </p><p><span class="kamma">
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_2264
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.28"
msgid "“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.29"
msgid "Ayaṃ patto itthannāmassa bhikkhuno nissaggiyo saṃghassa nissaṭṭho."
msgstr "This bowl that was to be relinquished by monk so-and-so has been relinquished to the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.30"
msgid "Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho imaṃ pattaṃ itthannāmassa bhikkhuno dadeyyā”ti."
msgstr "If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should give this bowl back to monk so-and-so.’"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="kamma">
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_2265
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.31"
msgid "Tena bhikkhunā sambahule bhikkhū upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā tukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassu vacanīyā—"
msgstr "After approaching several monks, that monk should put his upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the senior monks. He should then squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.32"
msgid "“ayaṃ me, bhante, patto dasāhātikkanto nissaggiyo."
msgstr "‘Venerables, this bowl that I have kept over ten days is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.33"
msgid "Imāhaṃ āyasmantānaṃ nissajjāmī”ti."
msgstr "I relinquish it to the venerables.’"

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.34"
msgid "Nissajjitvā āpatti desetabbā."
msgstr "After relinquishing it, he should confess the offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.35"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena āpatti paṭiggahetabbā,"
msgstr "The confession should be received by a competent and capable monk."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.36"
msgid "nissaṭṭhapatto dātabbo—"
msgstr "The relinquished bowl is then to be given back:"

#. HTML: </p><p><span class="kamma">
#. REF: sc15, ms1V_2266
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.37"
msgid "“Suṇantu me āyasmantā."
msgstr "‘Let the venerables listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.38"
msgid "Ayaṃ patto itthannāmassa bhikkhuno nissaggiyo āyasmantānaṃ nissaṭṭho."
msgstr "This bowl that was to be relinquished by monk so-and-so has been relinquished to you."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.39"
msgid "Yadāyasmantānaṃ pattakallaṃ, āyasmantā imaṃ pattaṃ itthannāmassa bhikkhuno dadeyyun”ti."
msgstr "If it seems appropriate to you, you should give this bowl back to monk so-and-so.’"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="kamma">
#. REF: sc16, ms1V_2267
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.40"
msgid "Tena bhikkhunā ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "After approaching a single monk, that monk should put his upper robe over one shoulder, squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.41"
msgid "“ayaṃ me, āvuso, patto dasāhātikkanto nissaggiyo."
msgstr "‘This bowl that I have kept over ten days is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.42"
msgid "Imāhaṃ āyasmato nissajjāmī”ti."
msgstr "I relinquish it to you.’"

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.43"
msgid "Nissajjitvā āpatti desetabbā."
msgstr "After relinquishing it, he should confess the offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.44"
msgid "Tena bhikkhunā āpatti paṭiggahetabbā,"
msgstr "The confession should be received by that monk."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.45"
msgid "nissaṭṭhapatto dātabbo—"
msgstr "The relinquished bowl is then to be given back:"

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.46"
msgid "“imaṃ pattaṃ āyasmato dammī”ti."
msgstr "‘I give this bowl back to you.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.46a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc17, ms1V_2268
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.47"
msgid "Dasāhātikkante atikkantasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than ten days and he perceives it as more than ten days, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.48"
msgid "Dasāhātikkante vematiko, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than ten days, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.49"
msgid "Dasāhātikkante anatikkantasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than ten days, but he perceives it as less than ten days, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.50"
msgid "Anadhiṭṭhite adhiṭṭhitasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it has not been determined, but he perceives it as determined, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.51"
msgid "Avikappite vikappitasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it has not been transferred, but he perceives it as transferred, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.52"
msgid "Avissajjite vissajjitasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it has not been given away, but he perceives it as given away, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.53"
msgid "Anaṭṭhe naṭṭhasaññī nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it has not been lost, but he perceives it as lost, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.54"
msgid "Avinaṭṭhe vinaṭṭhasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it has not been destroyed, but he perceives it as destroyed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.55"
msgid "Abhinne bhinnasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it has not been broken, but he perceives it as broken, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.56"
msgid "Avilutte viluttasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it has not been stolen, but he perceives it as stolen, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc18, ms1V_2269
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.57"
msgid "Nissaggiyaṃ pattaṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he uses a bowl that should be relinquished without first relinquishing it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.58"
msgid "Dasāhānatikkante atikkantasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is less than ten days, but he perceives it as more than ten days, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.59"
msgid "Dasāhānatikkante vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is less than ten days, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.60"
msgid "Dasāhānatikkante anatikkantasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is less than ten days and he perceives it as less than ten days, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.60a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc19, ms1V_2270
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.61"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

#. VAR: adhiṭṭheti → adhiṭṭhāti (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.62"
msgid "antodasāhaṃ adhiṭṭheti, vikappeti, vissajjeti, nassati, vinassati, bhijjati, acchinditvā gaṇhanti, vissāsaṃ gaṇhanti,"
msgstr "if within ten days it has been determined, transferred, given away, lost, destroyed, broken, stolen, or taken on trust;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.63"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:3.64"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc20, pts-cs-bu-np21.4, ms1V_2271
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:4.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū nissaṭṭhapattaṃ na denti."
msgstr "At one time monks from the group six did not give back a relinquished bowl."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.117
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:4.2"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the Master."

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:4.3"
msgid "“Na, bhikkhave, nissaṭṭhapatto na dātabbo."
msgstr "“Monks, a relinquished bowl should be given back."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:4.4"
msgid "Yo na dadeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti."
msgstr "If a monk doesn’t give it back, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc21, ms1V_2272
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np21:4.5"
msgid "Pattasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The first rule, the training rule on bowls, is finished."
